OL,6,F"That act of shaking caused severe and
OL,7,Firreversible brain injuries, she died
OL,8,F13 months later as a result of those
OL,9,Finjuries.
OL,11,F"The jury were sure that at the moment
OL,12,Fof shaking Everleigh you intended to
OL,13,Fcause her really serious injury."
OL,15,FAlong with brain injuries, Everleigh
OL,16,Falso had bone fractures, bruising to
OL,17,Fher face, atrophy to her eyes leading
OL,18,Fto her going blind, having spent the
OL,19,Fnight before in her father's care, the
OL,20,Fcourt heard.
