OL,6,FIn the sentencing hearing, Ms Marshall
OL,7,Fsaid: "The actual bodily harm
OL,8,Fundermines any suggestion that this
OL,9,Fwas one single act born of one
OL,10,Fmotivation and the motivation was
OL,11,Fdescribed by the defence as perhaps
OL,12,Ffrustration or flash of anger.
OL,14,F"We say that suggestion is undermined
OL,15,Fby the actual bodily harm."
OL,17,FWhile in the witness box, he often
OL,18,Fanswered questions to the effect of
OL,19,Fbeing unsure or not remembering what
OL,20,Fhad happened the night he attacked
OL,21,FEverleigh.
